Colombia Stocks: Coltejer, Ecopetrol Rise; Grupo Aval Declines

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o   a n d   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-03-28T20:53:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/colombia-stocks-coltejer-ecopetrol-rise-grupo-aval-declines.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:33 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.5 percent to 14,479.66, while the
Colcap Index dropped 0.4 percent to 1,721.70.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)   added 2.8 percent to 3,915 pesos.
 Colombia ’s state-run oil company will pay dividends of 145 pesos
($0.08) per share in installments from April 25 to October 25,
according to a company statement published on the country’s
securities regulator website.  Coltejer SA (COLTEJ)  , the Medellin-based clothing maker
and exporter, rose 1.2 percent to 85 centavos.  Mexico, Colombia, Chile and  Peru  will form a trade zone
with the “greatest possible free traffic of capital, services,
products and people,” Peru President Alan Garcia said in an
interview with Colombia’s El Tiempo newspaper.  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores (AVAL)  SA fell for a
second day, declining 1.1 percent to 1,355 pesos. The country’s
biggest financial holding company is selling between 800 million
and 1.6 billion preferred shares with a value of 1,300 pesos
each through April 11.  To contact the reporters on this story:
